[
    {
        "content": "<p>I am here to anounce that we formalized the definition of Gorenstein local ring and proved it is Cohen Macaulay in PR <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/30931\">#30931</a>. Our formalization follows the book \"Cohen-Macaulay rings\" proving <code>dim(M) &lt;= injdim(M) = depth(R)</code> for finitely generated module with finite injective dimension.<br>\nWe there are only few sorries left about map between <code>Ext</code> induced by an exact functor. (Commute with <code>mk_0</code>, <code>comp</code> and <code>extClass</code>)</p>",
        "id": 547131642,
        "sender_full_name": "Nailin Guan",
        "timestamp": 1761486141
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sorry, one more \"sorry\" : flat base change commute with <code>Hom</code> when finitely presented, do any one have good idea about how to implement?</p>",
