    {
        "content": "<p>We just finished all the separating, now the series consist of<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/30532\">#30532</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/30931\">#30931</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/31046\">#31046</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/31218\">#31218</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/31219\">#31219</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/31222\">#31222</a></p>",
        "id": 553430118,
        "sender_full_name": "Nailin Guan",
        "timestamp": 1762188140
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe not a very appropriate place, but some overview of all the related stuffs<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/XXP9KurtstrxEk1lqeG7PGHA/6a1c4ef01997ee0290a64602270d78d6.jpg\">6a1c4ef01997ee0290a64602270d78d6.jpg</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/XXP9KurtstrxEk1lqeG7PGHA/6a1c4ef01997ee0290a64602270d78d6.jpg\" title=\"6a1c4ef01997ee0290a64602270d78d6.jpg\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-original-dimensions=\"2160x1034\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/XXP9KurtstrxEk1lqeG7PGHA/6a1c4ef01997ee0290a64602270d78d6.jpg/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
        "id": 553654412,
        "sender_full_name": "Nailin Guan",
        "timestamp": 1762272311
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Some updates.<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/TZ7I20prjL5BAUbQQRDlgwd5/edc201e6ab6b7cec860523a467e16c24.jpg\">edc201e6ab6b7cec860523a467e16c24.jpg</a><br>\nThe next step would be proving Gorenstein local ring is stable under ring isomorphism. It turns out being a bit hard, as it involve relation of <code>Ext</code> over different rings.<br>\nFurther goal would be proving Gorenstein local ring is atable under localization.</p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/TZ7I20prjL5BAUbQQRDlgwd5/edc201e6ab6b7cec860523a467e16c24.jpg\" title=\"edc201e6ab6b7cec860523a467e16c24.jpg\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-original-dimensions=\"2062x992\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/TZ7I20prjL5BAUbQQRDlgwd5/edc201e6ab6b7cec860523a467e16c24.jpg/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
        "id": 556689715,
        "sender_full_name": "Nailin Guan",
        "timestamp": 1763303958
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We finished proving localization of Gorenstein local ring at prime is again Gorenstein.<br>\nThere are some refactor to the dependencies.<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/LGsRueAkypJHsxrGjWJC08sd/5c95d16afaa1e66b508d1761657df73e.jpg\">5c95d16afaa1e66b508d1761657df73e.jpg</a><br>\nNext step would be proving Gorenstein is stable under quotient by regular element and taking polynomial.</p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/LGsRueAkypJHsxrGjWJC08sd/5c95d16afaa1e66b508d1761657df73e.jpg\" title=\"5c95d16afaa1e66b508d1761657df73e.jpg\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-original-dimensions=\"2079x1079\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/LGsRueAkypJHsxrGjWJC08sd/5c95d16afaa1e66b508d1761657df73e.jpg/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
