    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We proved Gorenstein is stable under quotient by regular element in the PR proving it is CM, as a portion of the proof overlaps. Dependency is updated to the following.<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/ZjehKWP9aXWKvcF8ZqWczaU7/357721d493880aa0bd14eb10685aaa3e.jpg\">357721d493880aa0bd14eb10685aaa3e.jpg</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/ZjehKWP9aXWKvcF8ZqWczaU7/357721d493880aa0bd14eb10685aaa3e.jpg\" title=\"357721d493880aa0bd14eb10685aaa3e.jpg\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-original-dimensions=\"2094x1079\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/ZjehKWP9aXWKvcF8ZqWczaU7/357721d493880aa0bd14eb10685aaa3e.jpg/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
        "id": 560199304,
        "sender_full_name": "Nailin Guan",
        "timestamp": 1764087912
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We proved that polynomial over Gorenstein ring is Gorenstein.<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/VQGy5YP25uffE6rvMOIuw-iw/9d4b89eca702739422eb640fd7834091.jpg\">9d4b89eca702739422eb640fd7834091.jpg</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/VQGy5YP25uffE6rvMOIuw-iw/9d4b89eca702739422eb640fd7834091.jpg\" title=\"9d4b89eca702739422eb640fd7834091.jpg\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-original-dimensions=\"2120x1079\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/VQGy5YP25uffE6rvMOIuw-iw/9d4b89eca702739422eb640fd7834091.jpg/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
        "id": 560568060,
        "sender_full_name": "Nailin Guan",
        "timestamp": 1764240940
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As we currently not planning to move forward to dualizing complex, our reference almost ran out here, except the full version of the following (we currently have equivalece of 1, 1', 3).<br>\nIf anybody found other useful results about Gorenstein ring, feel free to pin me in this thread.<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/1ykVVL3fITtL6i3rC5Yx217s/.png\">图片.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/1ykVVL3fITtL6i3rC5Yx217s/.png\" title=\"图片.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"1837x1209\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/1ykVVL3fITtL6i3rC5Yx217s/.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
        "id": 560568140,
        "sender_full_name": "Nailin Guan",
        "timestamp": 1764240959
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>One more technical problem: what is the ideal way of decribing the <code>k</code> rank of <code>Ext(k,M)</code> (since it is annihilate by <code>m</code>)?<br>\nWe currently state it as <code>(⊤ : Submodule R ...).IsPrincipal</code> (we know it is nontrivial, so it is equivalent in this case)</p>",
